# Push After Changes

After making code, data, asset, or configuration changes, commit and push the completed work to GitHub unless the user explicitly says not to push.

- Include all files required for the change to work, including new product images or other assets referenced by edited code/data.
- Do not include unrelated local files unless they are needed for the requested change.
- Before committing, review `git status` and the diff so the commit only contains relevant work.
- Use a concise commit message that describes the user-facing outcome.
- If pushing requires approval, request approval and continue the push once approved.
